ENTRY            A0892   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A0892001   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 11         33
TITLE      Synthesis of the isotope 282-113 in the Np-237 + Ca-48
           fusion reaction
AUTHOR     (Yu.Ts.Oganessian, V.K.Utyonkov, Yu.V.Lobanov,
           F.Sh.Abdullin, A.N.Polyakov, R.N.Sagaidak,
           I.V.Shirokovsky, Yu.S.Tsyganov, A.A.Voinov,
           G.G.Gulbekian, S.L.Bogomolov, B.N.Gikal, A.N.Mezentsev,
           V.G.Subbotin, A.M.Sukhov, K.Subotic, V.I.Zagrebaev,
           G.K.Vostokin, M.G.Itkis, R.A.Henderson, J.M.Kenneally,
           J.H.Landrum, K.J.Moody, D.A.Shaughnessy, M.A.Stoyer,
           N.J.Stoyer, P.A.Wilk)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,76,011601,2007)
REL-REF    (R,,Yu.Ts.Oganessian,J,JP/G,34,R165,2007)
                                       Experimental conditions
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,1USALRL)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB) U-400 Cyclotron and gas-filled
            recoil separator
METHOD     (TOF)
SAMPLE     (93-NP-237,ENR=0.99) The target consisted of the
           enriched isotope 237Np, enrichment more than 99%,
           thickness 0.37 mg/cm2, deposited as an oxide onto
           1.5-um Ti foils.
DETECTOR   (MCPLT) A 4-cm x 12-cm semiconductor detector array
           with 12 vertical position-sensitive strips surrounded
           by eight 4-cm x 4-cm side detectors without position
           sensitivity, forming a box open to the front (beam)
           side. The position-averaged detection efficiency for
           full-energy alpha-particles emitted in the decays of
           implanted nuclei was 87%.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainties
HISTORY    (20110811C) SB
           (20170207A) SD: SF4 code was added to REACTION code in
           Subent 002. In REL-REF: JP/G,34,165 -> JP/G,34,R165.
           (20260204U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              33
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           36
SUBENT        A0892002   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                  5         13
REACTION   (93-NP-237(20-CA-48,3N)113-NH-282,,SIG)
DECAY-DATA (113-NH-282,73.MSEC,A,10630.)
           Half-life error is +134/-29 msec (measured)
           Alpha decay error is +-0.08 MeV (measured)
           This is the average alpha energy from 2/2 events
MISC-COL   (MISC-MIN) The excitation energy of the compound
           nucleus.
           (MISC-MAX) See above
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.Ts.Oganessian+,J,PR/C,76,011601,2007) Value
           from the text on p. 011601-3
HISTORY    (20110811C) SB
           (20170207A) SD: SF4 code was added to REACTION code.
           (20260204U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB              13
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 6          1
EN         DATA       +DATA-ERR  -DATA-ERR  MISC-MIN   MISC-MAX
MEV        PB         PB         PB         MEV        MEV
244.       0.9        1.6        0.6        36.9       41.2
ENDDATA              3
ENDSUBENT           21
